      "acceptanceCriteria": "SQA plan documented; version-controlled source code with change logs; regression test suite executed and passing for all relevant solver modules.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2) is commercial software with documented SQA processes. Version control records and release notes confirm the solver version used. A regression test suite covering the relevant turbulence and hemolysis sub-models was executed with all tests passing prior to the simulation campaign."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Code verification was performed using the method of manufactured solutions for the incompressible Navier-Stokes equations. Observed order of accuracy matched theoretical order, confirming correct implementation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) below 5% for primary QoI (relative hemolysis index); Richardson extrapolation applied across at least three mesh levels.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted with coarse (2.1M), medium (5.8M), and fine (14.2M) element counts. Richardson extrapolation yielded a GCI of 2.3% for the relative hemolysis index at the worst-case operating point, satisfying the 5% threshold. Achieved level 3 reflects quantified discretization uncertainty below 5%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Test conditions were generally representative of the COU. Flow rates and rotational speeds used in validation experiments span the 5 flow-speed combinations defined in the COU."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RH index within ±15% of experimental mean across all 5 operating points; no systematic bias exceeding one experimental standard deviation.",
      "rationale": "Predicted relative hemolysis index values were compared against experimental measurements from the FDA benchmark dataset. Agreement was within 12% at all operating points with no systematic directional bias identified, satisfying the ±15% criterion."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH), which directly maps to the clinical endpoint of blood cell damage. This QoI is standard in the CPB hemolysis literature and is directly comparable to the predicate device metric."
    },
